  title: Old Doll
  description: "Porcelain dolls were primarily made as decorative collector\u2019s
    items for adults rather than toys for children. Their fragile construction and
    detailed craftsmanship made them unsuitable for rough play, and they were often
    displayed in cabinets or kept as luxury objects. In contrast, children\u2019s
    ragdolls were much simpler, typically made from cloth or stuffed fabric, and
    were used as everyday playthings in the household. "
